# =============================================================================
# geometry/2D_multi_grain_test_p1.opts — P=1/C0 comparison mesh for
# 2D_multi_grain_test.opts (which uses P=2/C1 on the same 240x240 element
# grid). Same domain/grains/eps -- only basis degree/continuity differs.
#
# Generated by:
#   python3 preprocess/build_geometry_multi_grain.py --P 1 \
#     --out inputs/geometry/multi_grain_test_p1.dat \
#     --plot preprocess/multi_grain_geometry_p1.png \
#     --vtk preprocess/multi_grain_geometry_p1.vtk
#
# Motivation: with P=2/C1, the B-spline DOFs are control coefficients, not
# nodal values -- representing the ~8-element-wide tanh interface profile
# with a smooth C1 quadratic requires neighboring coefficients to overshoot
# [0,1] (spline "ringing"), which trips SNESSetFunctionDomainError (ice/air
# outside [phase_lo,phase_hi]) and causes the adaptive dt to oscillate
# (repeated "Reduce time step --> ... (rtol*=10 next time iteration)").
# With P=1/C0, DOFs are nodal values (interpolatory basis), directly bounded
# by the IC/AC physics -- this should let dt ramp further before hitting
# the bound check, and P=1 also has a smaller matrix bandwidth (cheaper
# ASM/ILU linear solves) than P=2/C1 at the same element count.
# =============================================================================
# DOF_GRID: 481 481
# (control-point grid of multi_grain_test_p1.dat: Nx+P = Ny+P = 480+1 -- used
# by run_permafrost.sh's compute_optimal_nprocs() since -geom_file overrides
# -Nx/-Ny and those default to 1.)
-geom_file inputs/geometry/multi_grain_test_p1.dat
-ic_type multi_grains
-dim 2
-Lx 4.0e-5
-Ly 4.0e-5
-p 1
-C 0
-Lz 0
-sed_grain_x 0.6e-5,2.0e-5,3.4e-5
-sed_grain_R 0.6e-5,0.6e-5,0.6e-5
-ice_grain_cx 0.0,4.0e-5,1.3e-5,2.7e-5
-ice_grain_cy 2.0e-5,2.0e-5,0.0,0.0
-ice_grain_R 6.0e-6,1.5e-5,4.0e-6,4.0e-6
-delt_t 1.0e-4
-eps 9.72e-08
-periodic 0
